&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 2 YEARS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a national Principal Project Manager to join our Service Transformation team working on national digital programmes of work, in NHS Wales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a senior project manager within the programme, the postholder will be responsible for working alongside the NHS Wales Collaborative to deliver the Radiology Informatics Systems Procurement, which is sponsored by the NHS Wales Collaborative Executive Group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This work is underpinned by the current Digital &lt;/span&gt;Health and Social Care Strategy - Informed Health and Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will require experience as a senior project manager and will be expected to apply their knowledge of the NHS as well as project management skills and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 25/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: David Sheard&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Assistant Director of Service Transformation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: david.sheard@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
